#compdef gqlgenc
# ============================================================================
# _gqlgenc — zsh completion for gqlgo's gqlgenc, the typed Go GraphQL
#             client codegen built on top of 99designs/gqlgen
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/Yamashou/gqlgenc
#   Module     : github.com/gqlgo/gqlgenc  (org redirect — repo serves
#                from Yamashou/gqlgenc but the Go module path is
#                gqlgo/gqlgenc)
#   Maintainer : Shohei Yamashita (Yamashou) + gqlgo org
#   License    : MIT
#   Stars      : 404
#   Language   : Go
#   Module     : github.com/gqlgo/gqlgenc
#   Binary     : gqlgenc  (root main.go; built from `go install
#                github.com/Yamashou/gqlgenc@latest`)
#   Last push  : 2026-05-07
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   gqlgenc is "a Go library for building GraphQL clients with
#   gqlgen" — Shohei Yamashita's CLIENT-side codegen built on top of
#   the gqlgen server-side toolchain.  Point it at a remote GraphQL
#   endpoint (or a local `.graphql` schema file) plus one or more
#   `.graphql` query/mutation/subscription documents, and it
#   produces fully typed Go structs for the variables and responses,
#   a typed `Client` struct with method-per-operation, and the
#   `client.Post()` plumbing that wraps the underlying HTTP
#   transport.  The default flag-based driver loads
#   `.gqlgenc.yml` (or `gqlgenc.yml`) from a configured directory
#   and writes the generated `.go` files in-place.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from main.go — uses stdlib `flag`
#                       package, NOT cobra/kong/clap-style
#                       sub-commands)
#   gqlgenc [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -version              Print the version string and exit
#     -c <DIR>              Directory holding the configuration file
#                           (shorthand for -configdir)  [default: .]
#     -configdir <DIR>      Directory holding the configuration file
#                                                       [default: .]
#
#   Standard Go flag-package conventions:
#     -h, --help            Show help (implicit in stdlib `flag`)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/99designs/gqlgen v0.17.73` and
#   `github.com/vektah/gqlparser/v2 v2.5.26` declared in go.mod —
#   gqlgen is the canonical Go GraphQL toolkit (Adam Scarr / Lasse
#   Westh-Nielsen / 99designs), shipping the gqlgen codegen,
#   gqlparser/v2 (canonical Go GraphQL AST + lexer + validator
#   maintained by the same author), and the model-first /
#   schema-first dual workflow that powers the majority of Go
#   GraphQL servers.  gqlgenc reuses the gqlgen `config`,
#   `codegen`, and template machinery to flip the codegen direction
#   from server-side resolvers to client-side typed query bindings.
#   gqlgenc's `clientv2/transport.go` defines the typed `Client`
#   struct with `Post(ctx, operationName, query, vars, headers,
#   response)` and a chainable `RequestInterceptor` pipeline;  the
#   generated bindings call `client.Post(ctx, ...)` once per
#   operation.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/Yamashou/gqlgenc/contents/go.mod
#       → github.com/99designs/gqlgen v0.17.73
#       → github.com/vektah/gqlparser/v2 v2.5.26
#       → module github.com/gqlgo/gqlgenc
#     gh api repos/Yamashou/gqlgenc/contents/main.go
#       → flag.Bool("version", ...) + flag.StringVar(configDir, "c",
#         ...) + flag.String("configdir", ".", ...)
#   This entry is the Go=138 leader bump that continues Axis 83
#   (GraphQL Client Library) opened at R921 with Rust=
#   graphql_client (graphql-rust/graphql-client).
#
#   No completion for `gqlgenc` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_gqlgenc() {
    _arguments \
        '-version[print the gqlgenc version and exit]' \
        '-c[configuration directory (shorthand)]:directory:_files -/' \
        '-configdir[configuration directory]:directory:_files -/' \
        '-h[show help]' \
        '--help[show help]'
}

_gqlgenc "$@"
